[789.120986, "o", "GIT SERVER SETUP COMPLETE\r\n=========================\r\n\r\nThe following components have been configured:\r\n\r\n1. Git Repository:\r\n   - Location: /git/server\r\n   - Type: Bare repository\r\n   - Owner: user:user\r\n\r\n2. Post-Receive Hook:\r\n   - Location: /git/server/hooks/post-receive\r\n   - Function: Automatically deploys pushed content to /var/www\r\n\r\n3. Web Server:\r\n   - Port: 8080\r\n   - Document Root: /var/www\r\n   - Type: Python HTTP Server (running in background)\r\n\r\n4. SSH Server:\r\n   - Status: Running\r\n   - Allows: git clone user@server:/git/server\r\n\r\n5. User Account:\r\n   - Username: user\r\n   - Password: password\r\n   - Permissions: Full access to /git/server and /var/www\r\n\r\n6. Hostname Resolution:\r\n   - 'server' resolves to 127.0.0.1 (localhost)\r\n\r\nUSAGE:\r\n------\r\nYou can now run the following commands:\r\n\r\n  git clone user@server:/git/server\r\n  cd server\r\n  echo \"hello world\" > hello.html\r\n  git add hello.html\r\n  git commit -m \"add hello.html\"\r\n  git push origin master\r\n  curl http://server:8080/hello.html\r\n\r\nThe file will be automatically deployed to the web server.\r\n"]
[789.121358, "o", "__CMDEND__79__\r\n"]
